<li>Operons involved in the cysteine biosynthetic pathway in the S. typhimurium CysB regulon include cysPUWAM , cysDNC , cysJIH , cysQ and cysK ( Fig. 1 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18957594" target="_blank">18957594</a>]<br></li>
<li>Genes of E. coli and S. Typhimurium involved in the sulfate / thiosulfate assimilatory pathway are shown according to the scheme of Kredich ; those activated by CysB ( as transcription units : sbp , cysPTWA , cysDNC , cysJIH , cysK , and cysM ) are highlighted in dark gray .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19727945" target="_blank">19727945</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19727945" target="_blank">19727945</a>]<br></li>
<li>CysB positively regulates the genes in sulfur assimilation and cysteine-biosynthesis when bound with NAS .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18957594" target="_blank">18957594</a>]<br></li>
<li>Exogenous cysteine also restores the antibiotic resistance phenotype , showing that cysteine and not those genes outside of cysteine-biosynthesis in the CysB regulon are important .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18957594" target="_blank">18957594</a>]<br></li>
<li>Cysteine biosynthesis is critical during periods of oxidative stress To further explore the connection of cysteine-biosynthesis to oxidative stress , we examined expression of genes in the CysB regulon during oxidative stress .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20600858" target="_blank">20600858</a>]<br></li>
<li>Residue threonine-149 of the Salmonella typhimurium CysB transcription activator : mutations causing constitutive expression of positively regulated genes of the cysteine regulon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19284970" target="_blank">19284970</a>]<br></li>
<li>The expression of the cysteine regulon is controlled by the CysB protein , which serves as a specific transcription activator for genes of the biosynthetic pathway ( 18 , 21 , 34 , 39 ) and as a repressor for its own gene , cysB ( 5 , 17 , 41 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1909324" target="_blank">1909324</a>]<br></li>
<li>Thus , CysB protein appears to have a dual regulatory role , first activator of as an genes of the L-cysteine biosynthetic pathway and second as a of its In this report , provide in vitro repressor own gene .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1706701" target="_blank">1706701</a>]<br></li>
<li>Shaded in light gray are the genes of E. coli participating in sulfonate -- sulfur-utilization ( transcription units tauABCD and ssuEADCB ) and requiring Cb1 ( as a direct activator ) and also CysB ( as an activator of the cbl gene ) according to a scheme adapted from Of these 21 down-regulated genes , 3.25-fold decrease was observed for treC which encodes trehalose-6-phosphate hydrolase and treB which encodes a trehalose-speciﬁc IIBC component of phosphotransferase system .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19727945" target="_blank">19727945</a>]<br></li>
<li>Microarray data from wild-type E. coli and soxR mutant cells exposed to paraquat show an increase in expression of all members of the CysB regulon involved in cysteine-synthesis upon exposure to paraquat and expression is greatest in the soxR mutant ( Pomposiello et al. , 2001 , 2003 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20600858" target="_blank">20600858</a>]<br></li>
<li>Since CysB is the regulator of sulphur-metabolism in the cells , a central metabolic pathway , it could be considered a global regulator in Salmonella Typhimurium .55 In addition , cysB and cysE mutants of Salmonella Typhimurium and E. coli have been reported to have increased resistance to mecillinam and novobiocin , which correlates with the results of this work , where a cysK mutant produced less cysteine , accumulated more H2S and hence was more resistant to oﬂoxacin ( Table 1 and Figure 4a and b ) .56 -- 60 In addition , these observations are in agreement with results obtained for a DcysK strain , which was 3-fold more resistant to ciproﬂoxacin in comparison with the Salmonella Typhimurium WT strain .53 Finally , a physiological role may be attributed to the regulation of CysK in the Salmonella infection cycle .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27530757" target="_blank">27530757</a>]<br></li>
<li>Heni-koff et al. ( 29 ) have recently recognized that these proteins and others [ E. coli IlvY , regulator of ilvC and other genes in the isoleucine-valine biosynthetic pathway ( 30 ) ; E. coli and S. typhimurium CysB , positive regulator of the cysteine regulon ( 31 ) ; S. typhimurium MetR , regulator of the metE and metH genes ( 32 ) ; and the Enterobacter cloacae ampR regulator of the ampC gene , which confers resistance to cepha-losporin ( 33 ) ] comprise a family of bacterial regulatory OxyR - A HT .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=2471187" target="_blank">2471187</a>]<br></li>
<li>Similar analysis demonstrated that disruption of the four-cysteine zinc ﬁnger motif of DksA by cysteine to serine point mutagenesis ( C114S ) signiﬁcantly reduced the activation of PcysD transcription in response to RNS ( Figure 5B ) and that CysB , a LysR-type transcriptional regulator fundamental to the control of sulfur-utilization and cysteine biosynthetic operons ( Schell , 1993 ) , is required for • NO - and DksA-dependent activation of PcysD in Salmonella exposed to RNS ( Figure 5C ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27065993" target="_blank">27065993</a>]<br></li>
<li>CysB regulates expression of the Salmonella typhimurium cysteine regulon , a group of 19 or more genes that function in the uptake and assimilatory reduction of oxidized forms of inorganic sulfur to sulﬁde , culminating in the incorporation of reduced sulfur into L-cysteine ( for reviews , see references 24 and 25 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7730263" target="_blank">7730263</a>]<br></li>
<li>Moreover , several genetic factors regulate the expression of cysK in addition to CysB , such as OmpR and CysE .54 CysK is produced at high levels and is thought to be the primary enzyme responsible for cysteine-synthesis ; however , CysM is the predominant enzyme catalysing the reaction in anaerobic conditions and when thiosulphate is present to react with O-acetyl - - serine ( OAS ) .48 L CysB binds the inducer N-acetyl-L-serine ( NAS ) , the product of a non-enzymatic rearrangement of OAS and inducer of the cysteine regulon , which activates genes involved in sulphate-assimilation , promoting more H2S synthesis .55 Moreover , serine transacetylase ( CysE ) is feedback inhibited by cysteine , providing kinetic control of the production of cysteine .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27530757" target="_blank">27530757</a>]<br></li>
<li>These investigations revealed that the activation of genes comprising cysteine-biosynthesis also occurs in response-to-hydrogen-peroxide , Received : 12 February 2016 Accepted : 18 March 2016 Published : 31 March 2016 is dependent upon the redox-sensing zinc ﬁnger motif of DksA , and requires the transcriptional regulator CysB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27065993" target="_blank">27065993</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of genes involved in cysteine-biosynthesis is controlled by the LysR-type transcriptional regulator CysB .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18957594" target="_blank">18957594</a>]<br></li>
<li>CysB , normally considered to be the central pleiotropic regulator of sulfur-metabolism in enteric bacteria , has been shown to be required for normal acid induction of arginine decarboxylase ( Shi & Bennett , 1994 ) as well as for sensitivity to novobiocin ( Rakonjac et al. , 1991 ) and mecillinam ( Oppezzo & Anto !	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11782505" target="_blank">11782505</a>]<br></li>
<li>In Escherichia coli , sbp is positively regulated by Cbl , a transcriptional regulator with 60 % amino acid similarity to CysB , involved in the regulation of cysteine-biosynthesis from organic sulfur sources ( Kredich , 1996 ; Stec et al. , 2006 ; Van Der Ploeg et al. , 1997 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18957594" target="_blank">18957594</a>]<br></li>
<li>Microarray analysis of E. coli during sulfur starvation found increased expression of ahpCF encoding an alkyl hydroperoxide reductase positively regulated by OxyR , and the CysB regulon has been shown by microarray analysis to be expressed in cells stressed by methyl viologen ( Blanchard et al. , 2007 ; Gyaneshwar et al. , 2005 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20600858" target="_blank">20600858</a>]<br></li>
